The paper deals with a problem related to computational geometry, specifically the VC-dimension of visibility regions in a simple polygon. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses epsilon-net theorems, which are related to discrete and computational geometry, and may fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves combinatorial arguments and graph theory, which may fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
